  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "DESIGN & COORDINATION ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your Role</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate design drawings with consultants to comply with requirements of the authorities</li>\n  <li>Review and provide solutions to technical problems as well as plan, monitor and report shop drawing production progress</li>\n  <li>Prepare technical submissions for materials, construction methods and C&amp;S shop drawings</li>\n  <li>Resolve construction issues on drawings and liaise closely with Architectural and M&amp;E teams as well as the authorities</li>\n  <li>Supervise a team of BIM Modelers for the production of coordinated shop drawings and Concrete Body Plans</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess a Degree in Civil/ Structural Engineering with relevant design working experience with contractors</li>\n  <li>Preferably a Professional Engineer registered with the Professional Engineers Board, Singapore</li>\n  <li>At least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li>\n  <li>Be conversant in British &amp; Singapore Design Standards</li>\n  <li>Be independent, analytical, highly motivated with excellent team spirit and interpersonal skills</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
